      • fillBundle

        public static Bundle fillBundle(Bundle outState,
                long geom,
                int numFields,
                boolean manualCoords,
                java.lang.String[] input,
                boolean enabled)
        Convenience method for adding extras to a bundle that can be passed to intents that start this activity.
        Parameters:
        outState - The bundle to add extras to. If null, a new Bundle will be created.
        geom - The id of the geometry to add attributes to. Must not be null.
        numFields - The number of non-geometry fields to display.
        manualCoords - Whether or not the coordinates (of a point) should be editable.
        input - A string array with text to pre-enter into the EditText boxes.
        enabled - Boolean deciding whether or not the EditText boxes should be enabled initially.

      • onClickSave

        public void onClickSave(View view)
        onClick callback method called when the Save attributes button is clicked.
        Parameters:

      • populateAttributeForm

        public void populateAttributeForm()

      • setupAttributeForm

        public void setupAttributeForm(java.lang.String[] input)
        Performs setup of the attribute form, setting the header and EditText contents. Must be called after populateAttributeForm().
        Parameters:
        input - A string array with any EditText content that should be entered.

      • enableAttributeForm
